00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:02,750
Why, with thousands of children
potentially falling off something lethal...

483
00:43:02,911 --> 00:43:06,621
...all around the world, would Superman
be in Niagara Falls today?

484
00:43:06,783 --> 00:43:08,124
Why not the Grand Canyon?

485
00:43:08,287 --> 00:43:11,964
- Ask the child's family. I'm sure they know.
- Why is it always when I'm with you...

486
00:43:12,127 --> 00:43:15,444
...until Superman appears?
And then you seem to disappear.

487
00:43:15,615 --> 00:43:19,193
- Very conveniently, it seems to me.
- I was out for hot dogs. For Pete's sake...

488
00:43:19,358 --> 00:43:21,944
When Superman appeared,
I looked at that hot dog stand...

489
00:43:22,110 --> 00:43:23,288
...and you were gone.

490
00:43:23,454 --> 00:43:24,598
- I was...
- Nowhere.

491
00:43:26,111 --> 00:43:27,965
I can't help it if I had to go to the...

492
00:43:28,766 --> 00:43:30,905
You are Superman, aren't you?

493
00:43:31,071 --> 00:43:34,419
Lois, look, we've been through
these hallucinations of yours before.

494
00:43:34,589 --> 00:43:36,313
Can't you see what you almost did?

495
00:43:36,478 --> 00:43:38,649
Throwing yourself off a building
30 stories high?

496
00:43:38,813 --> 00:43:40,952
Can't you see the tragic mistake
you almost made?

497
00:43:41,118 --> 00:43:44,892
Yeah, I made a mistake.
I made a mistake because...

498
00:43:46,686 --> 00:43:48,595
...I risked my life instead of yours.

499
00:43:48,765 --> 00:43:50,740
Lois, don't be insane.

500
00:43:50,909 --> 00:43:53,975
And don't fall down because
you're just gonna have to get up again.

501
00:43:54,141 --> 00:43:56,116
Lois, now, don't be crazy now. Lois!

502
00:44:08,477 --> 00:44:09,622
It is you.

503
00:44:15,612 --> 00:44:18,515
I guess I've known this
for the longest time.

504
00:44:21,277 --> 00:44:23,000
You realize, of course...

505
00:44:23,165 --> 00:44:26,034
...if you'd been wrong,
Clark Kent would have been killed.

506
00:44:27,869 --> 00:44:29,046
With a blank?

507
00:44:33,244 --> 00:44:34,389
Gotcha.

508
00:44:57,724 --> 00:45:00,309
A primitive sort of life form.

509
00:45:09,083 --> 00:45:10,260
Did you see that?

510
00:45:11,514 --> 00:45:13,620
Did you see what I did?

511
00:45:13,787 --> 00:45:16,241
I have powers beyond reason here.

512
00:45:16,538 --> 00:45:18,294
We all have them, my dear.

513
00:45:58,969 --> 00:46:01,968
- Wow, this is your home?
- No.

514
00:46:02,137 --> 00:46:05,072
Actually, I live in the city,
about three blocks from you.

515
00:46:06,489 --> 00:46:08,725
No, this is a very special place for me.

516
00:46:08,888 --> 00:46:11,092
I wanted you to see it.

517
00:46:11,481 --> 00:46:13,585
Listen, you warm enough?

518
00:46:14,809 --> 00:46:16,783
I guess I should be freezing, but I'm not.

519
00:46:16,952 --> 00:46:18,512
Good.

520
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:20,753
Come on, let me show you.

521
00:46:38,935 --> 00:46:40,080
I don't know.

522
00:46:40,984 --> 00:46:44,049
From the look of them,
I'll bet $10 they're from Los Angeles.

523
00:46:53,015 --> 00:46:56,724
Hey, you hippies,
get your butts off the road!

524
00:46:57,078 --> 00:47:00,045
I like the globe. It flashes
red like our Krypton sun.

525
00:47:00,438 --> 00:47:02,544
But not this irritating noise.

526
00:47:03,190 --> 00:47:04,945
Make way.

527
00:47:05,783 --> 00:47:07,474
Did I hear right?

528
00:47:07,639 --> 00:47:09,362
That son of a bitch give me an order?

529
00:47:09,879 --> 00:47:11,789
Duane, you take care of it.

530
00:47:16,631 --> 00:47:19,281
Just what in the hell
do you think you're doing here?

531
00:47:19,447 --> 00:47:21,389
What is this symbol?

532
00:47:21,559 --> 00:47:23,282
Do you follow another leader?

533
00:47:23,446 --> 00:47:25,682
Follow the leader?

534
00:47:26,806 --> 00:47:29,075
Holy skunk sweat.

535
00:47:29,238 --> 00:47:31,343
- All right.
- A weapon of some sort.

536
00:47:40,789 --> 00:47:42,448
How the hell did you do that?

537
00:47:49,781 --> 00:47:51,155
Jesus H. Christ.

538
00:47:53,589 --> 00:47:56,850
- That was good.
- I thought we might...

539
00:47:58,260 --> 00:48:00,748
...abandon the orange juice for once.

540
00:48:07,829 --> 00:48:10,381
- Here, cheers.
- Cheers.

541
00:48:14,516 --> 00:48:17,483
Must be tough being Clark Kent, isn't it?

542
00:48:17,844 --> 00:48:20,462
No. No, I really...

543
00:48:20,628 --> 00:48:22,700
I really like it sometimes.

544
00:48:22,867 --> 00:48:24,940
Even though I do
make a fool of myself.

545
00:48:26,579 --> 00:48:30,834
But, you know, if it weren't for him,
I never would have met you.

546
00:48:32,659 --> 00:48:35,955
But he is you.

547
00:48:36,692 --> 00:48:39,889
- It's kind of confusing.
- Not to me, it isn't.

548
00:48:42,227 --> 00:48:43,602
Everything's clear.

549
00:48:48,083 --> 00:48:51,694
Until yesterday, a middle-American town
that Middle America had forgotten.

550
00:48:51,859 --> 00:48:56,082
But today, the population...
Exaggerated reports put it at 123.

551
00:48:56,243 --> 00:48:57,617
- has increased by three.

552
00:48:57,778 --> 00:49:00,680
And these three new arrivals
bring destruction in their wake.

553
00:49:00,851 --> 00:49:03,436
As I look west into
East Houston this morning...

554
00:49:03,602 --> 00:49:06,668
<i>...I see a town gripped with fear.
- Who's the guy?</i>

555
00:49:06,834 --> 00:49:08,721
<i>Get that guy. Follow the guy.</i>

556
00:49:08,882 --> 00:49:10,443
<i>Who's the big guy?</i>

557
00:49:11,218 --> 00:49:13,040
<i>Okay, yeah, we've got a...</i>

558
00:49:13,362 --> 00:49:14,988
<i>- You got that?
- No.</i>

559
00:49:19,121 --> 00:49:20,845
<i>- That's fine.
- Try to wiggle it.</i>

560
00:49:21,010 --> 00:49:22,865
Who else is seeing this?

561
00:49:23,026 --> 00:49:26,735
Well, with this satellite linkup,
just about everybody. The whole planet.

562
00:49:26,897 --> 00:49:29,002
The whole planet Houston?

563
00:49:29,169 --> 00:49:32,398
Earth. The whole planet Earth.

564
00:49:34,608 --> 00:49:36,583
You may continue.

565
00:49:36,753 --> 00:49:40,266
As the extraordinary story continues...

566
00:49:41,265 --> 00:49:43,207
- Enough of this man.
- As this extraordinary...

567
00:49:43,377 --> 00:49:46,672
If the whole planet is watching,
let's show them something interesting.

568
00:49:46,832 --> 00:49:49,450
<i>Throw down your arms and surrender!</i>

569
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:52,367
<i>This is an order.</i>

570
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:57,735
General Zod does not
take orders. He gives them.

571
00:50:19,216 --> 00:50:22,086
He was in the line of that fire
and nothing happened to him.

572
00:50:22,256 --> 00:50:24,427
I haven't seen the likes
of this since Superman.

573
00:50:25,295 --> 00:50:26,954
<i>Yes? Yes.</i>

574
00:50:27,120 --> 00:50:31,659
<i>The Newsbeat control room has informed
me that a fleet of helicopter gunships is...</i>

575
00:50:31,824 --> 00:50:35,206
- Mr. President, sir, can't we...?
- There's nothing anybody can do.

576
00:50:35,375 --> 00:50:37,580
They have such powers,
nothing can stop them.

577
00:50:37,744 --> 00:50:39,118
Where's Superman?

578
00:50:39,279 --> 00:50:42,214
Where is he?
Why doesn't he do something?

579
00:50:54,127 --> 00:50:55,272
<i>Fire again.</i>

580
00:50:57,487 --> 00:50:58,893
<i>Fire again.</i>

581
00:51:01,998 --> 00:51:05,314
Look. They need machines to fly.

582
00:51:06,094 --> 00:51:08,647
<i>- Banking now.
- What bravery.</i>

583
00:51:08,974 --> 00:51:12,771
Be nice to them, my dear.
Blow them a kiss.

584
00:51:15,565 --> 00:51:18,151
<i>Rockets ready. Coming in on target.
Wait, wait.</i>

585
00:51:20,205 --> 00:51:21,350
<i>We're out of control.</i>

586
00:51:23,374 --> 00:51:26,537
<i>We're coming in, coming down.
Can't control it!</i>

587
00:51:26,701 --> 00:51:27,911
<i>We're coming down.</i>

588
00:51:33,677 --> 00:51:35,500
I win.

589
00:51:36,845 --> 00:51:38,853
I always win.

590
00:51:39,950 --> 00:51:43,145
Is there no one on
this planet to even challenge me?

591
00:52:02,316 --> 00:52:03,723
Come forward.

592
00:52:04,045 --> 00:52:05,867
Your general wishes to speak.

593
00:52:06,125 --> 00:52:10,183
I am General Zod, your ruler.

594
00:52:11,468 --> 00:52:15,330
Yes, today begins a new order!

595
00:52:15,596 --> 00:52:17,962
Your lands, your possessions...

596
00:52:18,123 --> 00:52:22,880
...your very lives will gladly be
given in tribute to me.

597
00:52:23,403 --> 00:52:25,476
In return for your obedience...

598
00:52:25,643 --> 00:52:28,196
...you will enjoy my generous protection.

599
00:52:28,362 --> 00:52:32,072
In other words,
you will be allowed to live.

600
00:52:34,474 --> 00:52:37,344
So you are a general?

601
00:52:38,347 --> 00:52:40,420
And who is your superior?

602
00:52:41,163 --> 00:52:46,083
- I answer only to the president.
- And he will answer to me.

603
00:52:47,306 --> 00:52:50,950
Or all of his cities
will end up like this one.

604
00:52:56,714 --> 00:53:00,193
Thousands of hours to create,
and they defaced it in seconds.

605
00:53:00,361 --> 00:53:03,361
Imagine what they'll do
to the world if we resist.

606
00:53:07,114 --> 00:53:10,310
<i>The people of your planet
are well-pleased with you, Kal-El.</i>

607
00:53:10,474 --> 00:53:14,052
<i>You have served them faithfully,
and they are grateful for it.</i>

608
00:53:15,881 --> 00:53:20,703
<i>And yet you have returned
to reason with me once again.</i>

609
00:53:23,081 --> 00:53:25,928
<i>My son, I have tried to anticipate
your every question.</i>

610
00:53:26,089 --> 00:53:27,846
<i>This was one I'd...</i>

611
00:53:29,225 --> 00:53:31,080
<i>I'd hoped you would not ask.</i>

612
00:53:34,121 --> 00:53:36,008
My attachment...

613
00:53:37,961 --> 00:53:43,046
...the feelings which I have developed
for a certain human being...

614
00:53:43,336 --> 00:53:45,572
...have deeply affected me, Father.

615
00:53:45,736 --> 00:53:50,013
<i>You cannot serve humanity by investing
your time and emotion in one human being...</i>

616
00:53:50,184 --> 00:53:52,224
<i>...at the expense of the rest.</i>

617
00:53:52,425 --> 00:53:57,028
<i>- The concepts are mutually exclusive.
- And...</i>

618
00:53:58,760 --> 00:54:02,786
...if I no longer wish
to serve humanity...

619
00:54:03,688 --> 00:54:06,983
<i>Is this how you repay their gratitude?</i>

620
00:54:07,143 --> 00:54:10,787
<i>By abandoning the weak,
the defenseless, the needy...</i>

621
00:54:10,951 --> 00:54:13,472
<i>...for the sake of your selfish pursuits?</i>

622
00:54:13,671 --> 00:54:16,966
Selfish? After all I've done for them?

623
00:54:17,127 --> 00:54:19,615
Will there ever come a time
when I've served enough?

624
00:54:19,783 --> 00:54:22,237
At least they get a chance for happiness.

625
00:54:22,406 --> 00:54:24,927
I only ask as much, no more.

626
00:54:25,638 --> 00:54:28,224
<i>Yours is a higher happiness.</i>

627
00:54:28,391 --> 00:54:32,580
<i>The fulfillment of your mission,
an inspiration you must have felt.</i>

628
00:54:33,158 --> 00:54:35,973
<i>You must have felt
that happiness within you.</i>

629
00:54:36,263 --> 00:54:39,263
<i>My son, surely you cannot
deny that feeling.</i>

630
00:54:39,623 --> 00:54:42,818
No, I cannot...

631
00:54:43,495 --> 00:54:47,171
...any more than I can deny the other,
which is stronger in me, Father.

632
00:54:48,550 --> 00:54:49,729
So much stronger.

633
00:54:55,494 --> 00:54:57,533
Is there no way then, Father?

634
00:54:58,150 --> 00:55:01,947
Must I finally be denied
the one thing in life which I truly desire?

635
00:55:03,558 --> 00:55:06,241
<i>If you will not be Kal-El...</i>

636
00:55:06,598 --> 00:55:08,452
<i>...if you will live as one of them...</i>

637
00:55:08,997 --> 00:55:10,907
<i>...love their kind as one of them...</i>

638
00:55:11,461 --> 00:55:13,566
<i>...then it follows that you must...</i>

639
00:55:14,245 --> 00:55:16,252
<i>...become one of them.</i>

640
00:55:43,587 --> 00:55:49,184
<i>This crystal chamber has in it the
harnessed rays of the red sun of Krypton.</i>

641
00:55:49,667 --> 00:55:51,009
<i>Once exposed to them...</i>

642
00:55:51,172 --> 00:55:54,553
<i>...all your great powers
on Earth will disappear.</i>

643
00:55:55,459 --> 00:55:56,888
<i>Forever.</i>

644
00:55:57,539 --> 00:55:59,481
<i>Once this is done, there's no going back.</i>

645
00:56:00,900 --> 00:56:03,201
<i>You will feel like an ordinary man.</i>

646
00:56:04,196 --> 00:56:07,131
<i>And you can be harmed
like an ordinary man.</i>

647
00:56:09,251 --> 00:56:11,040
<i>Think, Kal-El.</i>

648
00:56:12,420 --> 00:56:14,012
<i>I beg you.</i>

649
00:56:15,043 --> 00:56:16,604
Father...

650
00:56:17,795 --> 00:56:18,972
...I love her.

651
00:56:36,290 --> 00:56:37,719
<i>Think, Kal-El.</i>

652
00:58:29,759 --> 00:58:31,352
Come on. Come on.

653
00:58:41,789 --> 00:58:42,934
Look out!

654
00:59:32,060 --> 00:59:33,882
You are the one they call president?

655
00:59:34,620 --> 00:59:36,180
I am.

656
00:59:38,172 --> 00:59:41,881
I see you are practiced
in worshipping things that fly.

657
00:59:43,196 --> 00:59:44,821
Good.

658
00:59:45,659 --> 00:59:47,732
Rise before Zod.

659
00:59:51,547 --> 00:59:54,395
Now, kneel before Zod.

660
01:00:08,027 --> 01:00:09,489
You are not the president.

661
01:00:09,787 --> 01:00:14,358
No one who leads so many
could possibly kneel so quickly.

662
01:00:14,522 --> 01:00:16,245
I am the man they are protecting.

663
01:00:17,529 --> 01:00:19,318
I am the president.

664
01:00:20,218 --> 01:00:22,356
I'll kneel before you
if it will save lives.

665
01:00:22,778 --> 01:00:24,437
It will.

666
01:00:24,601 --> 01:00:27,056
Starting with your own.

667
01:00:30,617 --> 01:00:33,684
What a backward planet this must be...

668
01:00:34,106 --> 01:00:36,823
...where the men wear the ribbons...

669
01:00:37,337 --> 01:00:38,898
...and the jewelry.

670
01:00:51,801 --> 01:00:53,623
What I do now...

671
01:00:53,786 --> 01:00:56,851
...I do for the sake of
the people of the world.

672
01:00:57,017 --> 01:01:00,847
But there is one man here on Earth
who will never kneel before you.

673
01:01:01,145 --> 01:01:04,276
Who is this imbecile? Where is he?

674
01:01:04,441 --> 01:01:06,350
I wish I knew.

675
01:01:10,521 --> 01:01:11,830
Oh, God.

676
01:01:12,312 --> 01:01:13,773
Zod.

677
01:01:16,312 --> 01:01:17,686
Hey.

678
01:01:17,848 --> 01:01:20,270
You're awfully quiet over there.

679
01:01:21,912 --> 01:01:25,076
Yeah, I was just thinking...

680
01:01:25,240 --> 01:01:28,622
...I can't believe what
you've given up for me.

681
01:01:29,399 --> 01:01:32,782
Are you kidding? I didn't do
it for you, Lois, I did it for us.

682
01:01:33,367 --> 01:01:36,302
See, I told you there'd be
a hot dog place somewhere.

683
01:01:36,472 --> 01:01:40,246
Okay. It sure takes longer
when you can't fly.

684
01:01:40,408 --> 01:01:42,065
Hurry up.

685
01:01:42,231 --> 01:01:44,053
- Come on.
- Okay.

686
01:01:47,127 --> 01:01:49,363
Come on, it's my treat. Come on.

687
01:01:52,951 --> 01:01:55,219
Oh, boy, it's Mr. Wonderful.

688
01:01:56,791 --> 01:01:58,962
Thank you.

689
01:02:01,110 --> 01:02:03,729
- Do you have a men's room?
- Yeah. Right in the corner.

690
01:02:03,895 --> 01:02:06,317
- Want to sit down?
- Yeah.

691
01:02:08,215 --> 01:02:09,644
Hi, what would you folks like?

692
01:02:09,814 --> 01:02:13,262
I'd like a cheeseburger with
everything on it, and a Coke...

693
01:02:13,431 --> 01:02:16,944
...an order of fries
and a side salad, please.

694
01:02:17,942 --> 01:02:20,811
- And for you, sir?
- I'll think about it when I get back.

695
01:02:20,982 --> 01:02:22,444
Right. That's one cheeseburger...

696
01:02:22,678 --> 01:02:25,230
- Steak and eggs, over easy, coffee.
- Can I have my Coke?

697
01:02:25,398 --> 01:02:27,090
Coming right up.

698
01:02:27,446 --> 01:02:30,794
- I'm sorry, that seat's taken.
- It is now, sweetheart.

699
01:02:31,894 --> 01:02:33,781
Can I buy you something to eat?

700
01:02:34,422 --> 01:02:36,047
No, thank you.

701
01:02:36,918 --> 01:02:39,122
Excuse me. I think
you're sitting in my seat.

702
01:02:39,925 --> 01:02:42,315
Your seat's in there, four-eyes.

703
01:02:45,205 --> 01:02:48,915
Gee, I think perhaps somebody
ought to teach you some manners, sir.

704
01:02:50,005 --> 01:02:52,395
Yeah? Well, let me
know when he comes in.

705
01:02:52,565 --> 01:02:54,954
- Look, Clark, we can just...
- Honey.

706
01:02:56,213 --> 01:02:58,515
Excuse me, sir, would
you care to step outside?

707
01:02:58,708 --> 01:03:01,326
I said, excuse me, sir,
would you care to step outside?

708
01:03:04,468 --> 01:03:07,086
Now, listen, Rocky,
your steak's coming right up.

709
01:03:07,637 --> 01:03:11,248
Keep it on the flame, Ron.
This is just a minute steak.

710
01:03:12,436 --> 01:03:13,931
After you.

711
01:03:14,580 --> 01:03:16,368
- Clark.
- It's all right, honey.

712
01:03:19,540 --> 01:03:20,587
Clark!

713
01:03:22,707 --> 01:03:24,082
You all right, fella?

714
01:03:24,244 --> 01:03:26,894
He's gonna be fine,
just give me that.

715
01:03:27,219 --> 01:03:30,602
- Clark?
- Blood. It's my blood.

716
01:03:31,411 --> 01:03:35,438
I think maybe we ought to
hire a bodyguard from now on.

717
01:03:35,604 --> 01:03:38,920
I don't want a bodyguard.
I want the man I fell in love with.

718
01:03:39,092 --> 01:03:41,131
I know that, Lois.

719
01:03:41,299 --> 01:03:43,438
I wish he were here.

720
01:03:48,883 --> 01:03:50,541
Clark.

721
01:03:51,859 --> 01:03:54,958
Boy, you just don't have
enough sense to stay down, do you?

722
01:04:01,651 --> 01:04:05,677
You... You... You are no good.

723
01:04:06,387 --> 01:04:08,491
Settle down!

724
01:04:09,042 --> 01:04:11,376
I don't like your meat anyway.

725
01:04:13,458 --> 01:04:15,247
Oh, God.

726
01:04:22,034 --> 01:04:24,881
Clark? Clark?

727
01:04:25,042 --> 01:04:26,765
Clark, can you get up?

728
01:04:26,962 --> 01:04:29,514
- All right. Come on. I got you.
- Go slow. Go slow.

729
01:04:29,714 --> 01:04:31,404
Try and get up in that chair.

730
01:04:33,169 --> 01:04:35,723
- Sit down.
- I'm all right. I'm all right.

731
01:04:37,105 --> 01:04:40,553
Okay, everybody, he's all right.
Just relax. We'll have some fresh coffee.

732
01:04:40,721 --> 01:04:42,924
I'll turn the box on.

733
01:04:43,729 --> 01:04:46,446
<i>We interrupt this program
for an urgent message...</i>

734
01:04:46,609 --> 01:04:49,391
<i>...from the President
of the United States.</i>

735
01:04:49,616 --> 01:04:51,853
<i>This is your president.</i>

736
01:04:52,113 --> 01:04:56,749
<i>On behalf of my country, and in the
name of the other leaders of the world...</i>

737
01:04:57,232 --> 01:04:59,849
<i>...with whom I have today consulted...</i>

738
01:05:00,367 --> 01:05:03,019
<i>...I hereby abdicate...</i>

739
01:05:03,248 --> 01:05:07,340
<i>...all authority and
control over this planet...</i>

740
01:05:07,856 --> 01:05:09,318
<i>...to General Zod.</i>

741
01:05:10,096 --> 01:05:11,242
Zod.

742
01:05:11,409 --> 01:05:14,791
<i>Only by strict compliance
with all his directions...</i>

743
01:05:15,568 --> 01:05:19,365
<i>...will the lives of
innocent millions be spared.</i>

744
01:05:19,888 --> 01:05:21,415
<i>Superman, can you hear me?</i>

745
01:05:21,585 --> 01:05:25,196
<i>- Superman, where?
- Who is this Superman?</i>

746
01:05:25,360 --> 01:05:31,175
<i>- You'll find out. And when you do...
- Come to me, Superman, if you dare.</i>

747
01:05:31,343 --> 01:05:32,870
<i>I defy you.</i>

748
01:05:33,040 --> 01:05:36,355
<i>Come! Come and kneel before Zod.</i>

749
01:05:38,704 --> 01:05:40,077
<i>Zod!</i>

750
01:05:41,583 --> 01:05:43,274
- Here? When?
- When?

751
01:05:43,439 --> 01:05:47,051
Where the hell have you been, Mac?
On a desert island?

752
01:05:49,678 --> 01:05:51,336
I have to go back.

753
01:05:51,502 --> 01:05:53,390
You can't go back.

754
01:05:53,551 --> 01:05:55,972
- There's no way now.
- I have to.

755
01:05:56,142 --> 01:05:59,209
I've gotta try, damn it. I've
gotta try something, anything.

756
01:05:59,375 --> 01:06:02,124
It's not your fault.

757
01:06:02,287 --> 01:06:05,548
You didn't know this was gonna happen.

758
01:06:06,894 --> 01:06:08,650
He knew.

759
01:06:08,814 --> 01:06:10,985
I heard him.

760
01:06:11,149 --> 01:06:13,321
I just didn't listen.

761
01:06:29,293 --> 01:06:31,780
You're master of all you survey.

762
01:06:31,980 --> 01:06:33,837
And so I was yesterday.

763
01:06:33,998 --> 01:06:36,386
And the day before.

764
01:06:49,773 --> 01:06:50,918
Hello, there.

765
01:06:52,428 --> 01:06:54,251
Lex Luthor.

766
01:06:56,557 --> 01:06:58,596
Lex Luthor.

767
01:06:59,052 --> 01:07:01,834
You've heard the name?
The greatest criminal mind on Earth.

768
01:07:02,348 --> 01:07:04,869
I told you this was a puny planet.

769
01:07:05,036 --> 01:07:06,596
Wait just a moment.

770
01:07:06,764 --> 01:07:09,764
Wait until you get to know
me better. Will you, please?

771
01:07:09,932 --> 01:07:13,477
Wait. Look, I can give
you anything you want.

772
01:07:13,644 --> 01:07:15,554
I can give you the brass ring...

773
01:07:15,723 --> 01:07:20,262
...the unlimited freedom
to maim, kill, destroy.

774
01:07:20,748 --> 01:07:25,155
Plus, Lex Luthor's keen mind.
Lex Luthor's savvy.

775
01:07:25,323 --> 01:07:29,479
Lex Luthor's career guidance.
Lex Luthor's School of Better...

776
01:07:31,307 --> 01:07:33,673
We have all of this without you.

777
01:07:34,442 --> 01:07:36,515
You cannot bargain
with what you don't have.

778
01:07:37,194 --> 01:07:39,266
Magnificent One...

779
01:07:40,203 --> 01:07:43,464
...what I am bargaining with
is what you do not have.

780
01:07:43,626 --> 01:07:44,935
The son of Jor-El.

781
01:07:48,586 --> 01:07:50,790
The son of Jor-El?

782
01:07:51,146 --> 01:07:52,575
I said that, didn't I?

783
01:07:53,066 --> 01:07:55,619
Jor-El, our jailer?

784
01:07:55,850 --> 01:07:57,922
No, Jor-El, the baseball player.

785
01:07:58,090 --> 01:07:59,999
Yes, Jor-El, your jailer.

786
01:08:00,297 --> 01:08:03,647
- The son of Jor-El? On this planet?
- Aye.

787
01:08:03,819 --> 01:08:06,307
<i>Possibly you know him better
by his nom de voyage...</i>

788
01:08:06,475 --> 01:08:09,441
...or his name he travels under:

789
01:08:09,610 --> 01:08:11,334
Superman.

790
01:08:13,546 --> 01:08:15,138
So this is Superman.

791
01:08:16,426 --> 01:08:17,670
How do you know of Jor-El?

792
01:08:17,834 --> 01:08:22,089
My Fullness, as I
explained to you before...

793
01:08:23,114 --> 01:08:24,543
...I'm about the best there is.

794
01:08:24,713 --> 01:08:25,957
Revenge.

795
01:08:26,121 --> 01:08:28,031
We will kill the son of our jailer.

796
01:08:28,201 --> 01:08:31,048
- Revenge.
- Revenge! Now we're cooking.

797
01:08:31,241 --> 01:08:33,151
- He flies, then?
- Constantly.

798
01:08:33,322 --> 01:08:35,263
- He has powers as we do?
- Certainly.

799
01:08:35,433 --> 01:08:39,589
But, Magnificent One...

800
01:08:39,752 --> 01:08:42,470
...he's just one...

801
01:08:42,633 --> 01:08:45,087
...where you are three.

802
01:08:45,800 --> 01:08:49,062
- Or four, if you count him twice.
- We will bring him to his knees.

803
01:08:49,320 --> 01:08:50,913
Wait!

804
01:08:52,424 --> 01:08:53,634
First, you must find him.

805
01:08:53,928 --> 01:08:57,093
And Lex Baby is the only
one who knows where he is.

806
01:08:58,568 --> 01:09:00,957
What do you want?

807
01:09:01,160 --> 01:09:03,200
Well, general...

808
01:09:03,368 --> 01:09:05,823
...the world is a big place.

809
01:09:05,991 --> 01:09:08,326
Thank goodness...

810
01:09:08,488 --> 01:09:10,375
...my needs are small.

811
01:09:11,751 --> 01:09:17,348
As it turns out, I have this
affinity for beachfront property.

812
01:09:19,015 --> 01:09:21,403
What do you want?

813
01:09:21,575 --> 01:09:23,266
Australia.

814
01:09:53,509 --> 01:09:54,972
Hey.

815
01:09:57,605 --> 01:10:01,883
Listen... Hey, come on,
where are you...? Please!

816
01:10:37,924 --> 01:10:39,450
Father?

817
01:10:41,957 --> 01:10:43,931
If you can hear me...

818
01:10:45,572 --> 01:10:47,394
...I failed.

819
01:10:49,699 --> 01:10:51,522
I failed you...

820
01:10:51,812 --> 01:10:53,503
...I failed myself...

821
01:10:55,298 --> 01:10:57,306
...and all humanity.

822
01:11:00,098 --> 01:11:02,172
I've traded my birthright...

823
01:11:03,236 --> 01:11:07,840
...for a life of submission in a world
that's now ruled by your enemies.

824
01:11:09,476 --> 01:11:11,865
There's nobody left to help them now...

825
01:11:12,643 --> 01:11:14,498
...the people of the world.

826
01:11:15,523 --> 01:11:17,465
Not since I...

827
01:11:18,339 --> 01:11:21,339
Father!

828
01:12:29,488 --> 01:12:33,897
<i>Listen carefully, my son,
for we shall never speak again.</i>

829
01:12:35,696 --> 01:12:38,184
<i>If you hear me now...</i>

830
01:12:38,352 --> 01:12:41,254
<i>...then you have made use
of the only means left to you:</i>

831
01:12:42,128 --> 01:12:45,903
<i>The crystal source through which
our communications begun.</i>

832
01:12:46,832 --> 01:12:49,134
<i>The circle is now complete.</i>

833
01:12:49,488 --> 01:12:52,553
<i>You have made a dreadful mistake, Kal-El.</i>

834
01:12:55,824 --> 01:12:59,207
<i>You did this of your own free will...</i>

835
01:12:59,727 --> 01:13:02,410
<i>...in spite of all I could say
to dissuade you.</i>

836
01:13:04,623 --> 01:13:06,149
I...

837
01:13:06,319 --> 01:13:10,629
<i>Now you have returned to me
for one last chance to redeem yourself.</i>

838
01:13:10,799 --> 01:13:15,501
<i>This too finally I have anticipated,
my son.</i>

839
01:13:18,062 --> 01:13:20,135
<i>Look at me, Kal-El.</i>

840
01:13:22,478 --> 01:13:26,886
<i>Once before when you were small,
I died...</i>

841
01:13:28,077 --> 01:13:30,925
<i>...while giving you a chance for life.</i>

842
01:13:32,013 --> 01:13:35,810
<i>And now, even though it will exhaust
the final energy left within me...</i>

843
01:13:36,494 --> 01:13:38,250
Father, no.

844
01:13:39,693 --> 01:13:42,060
<i>Look at me, Kal-El.</i>

845
01:13:44,685 --> 01:13:49,289
<i>The Kryptonian prophecy
will be at last fulfilled.</i>

846
01:13:49,581 --> 01:13:54,883
<i>The son becomes the father,
the father becomes the son.</i>

847
01:13:59,212 --> 01:14:02,955
<i>Farewell forever, Kal-El.</i>

848
01:14:06,094 --> 01:14:08,460
<i>Remember me, my son.</i>

849
01:14:37,260 --> 01:14:38,786
My son.

850
01:14:53,739 --> 01:14:55,364
Father!

851
01:15:08,458 --> 01:15:11,774
Harold. Coffee, black, no sugar.

852
01:15:11,945 --> 01:15:14,913
Black, no sug... Yeah. Yeah.

853
01:15:15,754 --> 01:15:17,247
Who's paying, huh?

854
01:15:18,250 --> 01:15:20,868
No, no! There's three of them.
That cockamamie general...

855
01:15:21,034 --> 01:15:24,995
...and a big truck with hair on it and a broad
that looks like the queen of the runway.

856
01:15:25,162 --> 01:15:29,701
They can fly, they can see through things.
Anything Superman can do, they can do.

857
01:15:30,153 --> 01:15:32,358
Where is he, anyway?

858
01:15:32,554 --> 01:15:34,464
Maybe he hasn't heard
about it yet, chief.

859
01:15:34,634 --> 01:15:36,706
- Maybe...
- Maybe he's just run out of guts.

860
01:15:36,874 --> 01:15:39,394
- No sugar. And don't call me "chief."
- He'll be here.

861
01:15:39,562 --> 01:15:42,944
- If there's any way at all, he'll be here.
- Yeah, he'll be here.

862
01:15:45,386 --> 01:15:47,557
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

863
01:15:48,233 --> 01:15:50,055
- Hey, Charlie, you feel that?
- Yeah.

864
01:15:50,345 --> 01:15:51,686
Sounds like an earthquake.

865
01:15:53,706 --> 01:15:55,199
Oh, my!

866
01:16:01,065 --> 01:16:03,617
- It's those three.
- Stop!

867
01:16:03,784 --> 01:16:06,948
- Oh, my God, they're here now!
- Oh, no!

868
01:16:18,056 --> 01:16:19,233
This is scary!

869
01:17:06,311 --> 01:17:08,351
You all right, chief?

870
01:17:08,839 --> 01:17:10,180
Hi.

871
01:17:12,039 --> 01:17:14,821
You should see the White House.
They'll be cleaning for months.

872
01:17:14,982 --> 01:17:16,259
Lex Luthor.

873
01:17:16,806 --> 01:17:17,984
Wouldn't you know it?

874
01:17:18,598 --> 01:17:21,316
This is the son of Jor-El?

875
01:17:21,479 --> 01:17:23,300
- No, but I bet you're a son of a...
- Jimmy!

876
01:17:24,486 --> 01:17:27,355
You promised me the son of Jor-El.

877
01:17:28,773 --> 01:17:29,886
Yes, Your Grace.

878
01:17:30,470 --> 01:17:33,917
But what I've given
you is the next best thing.

879
01:17:34,085 --> 01:17:36,988
You just hold on to that
little lady, and he'll be along.

880
01:17:37,157 --> 01:17:38,651
See, they have this relationship.

881
01:17:38,821 --> 01:17:42,977
She does all his public relations,
and he gives her every exclusive.

882
01:17:43,141 --> 01:17:45,694
They're the best of friends.
You know what I mean?

883
01:17:46,021 --> 01:17:49,119
What an undemanding
male this Superman must be.

884
01:17:49,540 --> 01:17:52,061
You could use a tuck
here and there yourself, sister.

885
01:17:52,549 --> 01:17:54,076
Wait!

886
01:17:54,244 --> 01:17:55,553
- I'm sorry!
- She lives for now.

887
01:17:56,452 --> 01:17:58,721
Kill the rest, starting with him.

888
01:18:01,155 --> 01:18:03,545
Wait. Wait, wait, wait!

889
01:18:03,717 --> 01:18:05,210
Wait. Wait.

890
01:18:05,380 --> 01:18:09,308
Don't you remember the White House?
The Oval Room? We had a few laughs there.

891
01:18:09,860 --> 01:18:11,353
You ought to have that fixed.

892
01:18:22,467 --> 01:18:23,613
General...

893
01:18:24,484 --> 01:18:26,523
...haven't you heard
of freedom of the press?

894
01:18:26,722 --> 01:18:28,665
- Superman!
- Superman, thank God.

895
01:18:29,603 --> 01:18:30,912
I mean, get him!

896
01:18:31,300 --> 01:18:33,056
Come to me, son of Jor-El!

897
01:18:33,540 --> 01:18:36,256
Kneel before Zod!

898
01:18:50,275 --> 01:18:52,184
Watch out. You all right?

899
01:19:10,978 --> 01:19:12,471
Son of Jor-El.

900
01:19:12,930 --> 01:19:15,385
We were beginning to
think you were a coward.

901
01:19:15,746 --> 01:19:16,956
I'm not a coward, Zod.

902
01:19:17,218 --> 01:19:20,153
It is extremely likely
you are merely a fool.

903
01:19:20,322 --> 01:19:22,591
Like father, like son.

904
01:19:38,208 --> 01:19:39,549
Look out!

905
01:19:42,497 --> 01:19:45,148
Then die as you deserve to!

906
01:19:54,880 --> 01:19:56,986
Come on, come on, Superman! Get him!

907
01:19:57,248 --> 01:19:59,222
Man, this is gonna be good.

908
01:20:33,759 --> 01:20:35,285
<i>Superman.</i>

909
01:20:55,454 --> 01:20:57,724
- Hey, that's the chief's.
- The chief's got it.

910
01:21:06,077 --> 01:21:07,965
What, you hit a woman?

911
01:21:30,140 --> 01:21:33,175
Oh, my God! My baby!

912
01:21:33,534 --> 01:21:35,867
Help my baby!

913
01:21:38,621 --> 01:21:40,246
Thank you.

914
01:21:41,757 --> 01:21:45,172
This Superman is nothing of the kind.

915
01:21:45,373 --> 01:21:47,674
- I've discovered his weakness.
- Yes.

916
01:21:47,836 --> 01:21:49,179
He cares.

917
01:21:49,437 --> 01:21:52,567
He actually cares
for these Earth people.

918
01:21:52,732 --> 01:21:55,766
- Like pets?
- I suppose so.

919
01:22:03,612 --> 01:22:05,435
I'll draw his fire...

920
01:22:05,596 --> 01:22:07,450
...with some of my own.

921
01:22:33,882 --> 01:22:35,475
What's happening to those cars?

922
01:22:38,778 --> 01:22:40,186
Get out of the way!

923
01:23:52,280 --> 01:23:53,327
Superman.

924
01:24:37,014 --> 01:24:38,356
Oh, thank you!

925
01:24:38,519 --> 01:24:40,974
I never thought this thing
would go the distance.

926
01:24:54,614 --> 01:24:56,621
No! Don't do it!

927
01:24:57,046 --> 01:24:58,638
The people!

928
01:25:03,093 --> 01:25:04,817
Throw it!

929
01:25:25,173 --> 01:25:28,336
- Get away from there. Get away from there.
- Let's help them out!

930
01:25:31,732 --> 01:25:35,048
- I got her. I got her. Don't worry.
- He's dead.

931
01:25:36,629 --> 01:25:38,538
Superman is dead.

932
01:25:41,652 --> 01:25:42,862
They've killed Superman.

933
01:25:44,243 --> 01:25:46,448
- He's dead.
- Let's go get them!

934
01:25:46,612 --> 01:25:49,099
- Come on, we'll show them!
- I know some judo. Let's go!

935
01:25:49,619 --> 01:25:51,081
Come on!

936
01:26:20,275 --> 01:26:22,796
I'm holding it, I'm holding it!

937
01:26:22,962 --> 01:26:25,264
What can you do if
you can't see what's happening?

938
01:26:30,034 --> 01:26:33,034
- Hold on!
- Oh, my God!

939
01:27:39,120 --> 01:27:41,487
You can't leave us!

940
01:27:46,000 --> 01:27:50,124
So he is a coward after all.

941
01:27:50,512 --> 01:27:51,973
He's gone.

942
01:27:52,143 --> 01:27:53,605
Come back, Superman!

943
01:27:58,479 --> 01:28:00,073
Don't leave us!

944
01:28:02,863 --> 01:28:04,773
He chickened out.

945
01:28:05,264 --> 01:28:06,278
Phony!

946
01:28:07,567 --> 01:28:09,422
Superman didn't even do nothing.

947
01:28:09,679 --> 01:28:11,718
Come on, let's go.

948
01:28:18,446 --> 01:28:22,091
- There they are.
- Get away from here. Jimmy.

949
01:28:30,735 --> 01:28:32,490
Our victory is complete.

950
01:28:32,654 --> 01:28:34,344
The son of Jor-El has fled.

951
01:28:34,509 --> 01:28:37,095
- Superman fled?
- I don't believe you.

952
01:28:37,261 --> 01:28:41,156
You heard him. Three against one,
you should've taken two ears and a tail.

953
01:28:41,326 --> 01:28:44,292
- He fled in fear of us.
- He'll be back.

954
01:28:44,461 --> 01:28:46,730
As long as he's alive,
he's gonna try again.

955
01:28:46,893 --> 01:28:50,189
- The next time, we will kill him.
- The next time?

956
01:28:51,181 --> 01:28:53,156
The next time?

957
01:28:53,869 --> 01:28:55,877
What am I gonna do with you people?

958
01:28:56,045 --> 01:28:58,533
I held up my end.
I delivered you the blue boy.

959
01:28:58,700 --> 01:29:00,906
What do I get from my triple threat?

960
01:29:01,070 --> 01:29:05,225
"Bow, yield, kneel."
That kind of stuff closes out a town.

961
01:29:06,733 --> 01:29:10,377
Why do you say this to me
when you know I will kill you for it?

962
01:29:10,572 --> 01:29:14,217
Kill me? Lex Luthor?

963
01:29:14,637 --> 01:29:17,288
Extinguish the greatest
criminal flame of our age?

964
01:29:17,453 --> 01:29:21,414
- Eradicate the only man on earth with...
- Let me kill him!

965
01:29:21,868 --> 01:29:23,395
- Superman's address?

966
01:29:27,117 --> 01:29:32,234
What more do you want?
I can see the greed written on your face.

967
01:29:32,396 --> 01:29:35,145
A small incentive, O Fullest One.

968
01:29:35,307 --> 01:29:38,209
A mere bauble to jog the memory.

969
01:29:38,795 --> 01:29:39,940
What more?

970
01:29:40,875 --> 01:29:42,021
Cuba.

971
01:29:49,707 --> 01:29:55,686
I trust you are not wasting my time,
Lex Luthor.

972
01:29:55,882 --> 01:29:58,021
Of course not, Your Turbulence.

973
01:30:42,313 --> 01:30:44,321
Show yourself, coward!

974
01:30:47,113 --> 01:30:49,219
Son of a coward!

975
01:30:55,338 --> 01:30:56,581
I'm here, Zod.

976
01:30:56,969 --> 01:30:59,871
- Let Miss Lane go, step inside. We'll talk.
- No, don't, Superman!

977
01:31:00,041 --> 01:31:01,928
Please don't listen to him. He's just...

978
01:31:02,345 --> 01:31:03,555
Stop.

979
01:31:03,721 --> 01:31:05,631
Your powers are identical to mine.

980
01:31:05,800 --> 01:31:08,898
But we are three.
We could tear you limb from limb.

981
01:31:09,193 --> 01:31:10,370
Do it, Your Grace.

982
01:31:10,729 --> 01:31:12,801
Just grab a leg and just make a wish.

983
01:31:14,248 --> 01:31:16,550
But you are victim
to another fatal weakness...

984
01:31:16,968 --> 01:31:18,342
...your compassion.

985
01:31:18,504 --> 01:31:20,871
The death of others
means more to you than your own.

986
01:31:21,032 --> 01:31:22,439
Yes, with rare exceptions.

987
01:31:22,856 --> 01:31:28,158
Your father condemned us to an eternal
living death. Your fate will be the same.

988
01:31:28,424 --> 01:31:30,399
You will live, Kal-El, forever...

989
01:31:30,568 --> 01:31:35,357
...as my slave. If not, then others
will pay for your obstinate attitude.

990
01:31:35,528 --> 01:31:40,830
Innocent people, millions if necessary,
beginning with this Lois person.

991
01:31:40,999 --> 01:31:42,559
- Don't, Superman, don't!
- Stop it!

992
01:31:46,599 --> 01:31:48,737
All right, Zod.

993
01:31:49,382 --> 01:31:50,757
It's over.

994
01:31:53,478 --> 01:31:57,090
Your Grace, don't believe him!
You don't know him the way that I do.

995
01:31:59,206 --> 01:32:01,312
I sense the presence of Jor-El here.

996
01:32:03,239 --> 01:32:05,027
We will destroy this place.

997
01:32:05,512 --> 01:32:06,853
And then kill him.

998
01:32:09,062 --> 01:32:10,851
Him.

999
01:32:11,975 --> 01:32:14,789
Him? Me?

1000
01:32:16,134 --> 01:32:17,989
General, this is Lex Luthor.

1001
01:32:18,630 --> 01:32:22,046
Remember...?
I helped you through the tough times.

1002
01:32:22,214 --> 01:32:24,002
I filled your inside straight.

1003
01:32:24,517 --> 01:32:28,412
You came to me with nothing.
I gave you Superman.

1004
01:32:28,582 --> 01:32:29,988
Silence!

1005
01:32:30,149 --> 01:32:31,677
Well, look...

1006
01:32:34,085 --> 01:32:35,547
Guy's a clod.

1007
01:32:36,133 --> 01:32:38,109
You think you know people, right?

1008
01:32:38,693 --> 01:32:41,694
Promises were made,
gifts were exchanged.

1009
01:32:41,861 --> 01:32:45,122
I gotta hand it to you, you know.
You always told the truth.

1010
01:32:45,317 --> 01:32:48,001
A guy always knew
where he stood with you.

1011
01:32:50,021 --> 01:32:52,771
Try to get them all
into this molecule chamber here.

1012
01:32:52,933 --> 01:32:54,972
It takes away their powers, see...

1013
01:32:55,140 --> 01:32:57,628
...and turns them into
ordinary human beings.

1014
01:32:57,797 --> 01:32:58,942
Now, if you could...

1015
01:33:01,988 --> 01:33:05,054
- Don't go in there. It's a trap.
- Luthor, you poisonous snake!

1016
01:33:05,412 --> 01:33:06,841
That's a molecule chamber.

1017
01:33:07,044 --> 01:33:10,721
It makes people like
you into people like me.

1018
01:33:11,140 --> 01:33:13,245
- You've done well, Lex Luthor.
- I thought so.

1019
01:33:14,404 --> 01:33:15,930
Seize him.

1020
01:33:17,540 --> 01:33:19,579
- Kill her.
- No! Superman, no!

1021
01:33:19,747 --> 01:33:21,787
All right! All right, leave her alone, Zod!

1022
01:33:22,307 --> 01:33:23,901
You win.

1023
01:33:26,979 --> 01:33:31,355
General, the crystal there
activates the mechanism.

1024
01:33:31,523 --> 01:33:34,241
Lex Luthor, ruler of Australia...

1025
01:33:34,404 --> 01:33:36,029
...activate the machine.

1026
01:33:46,755 --> 01:33:48,665
With your permission.

1027
01:34:58,816 --> 01:35:01,566
And now, finally...

1028
01:35:05,633 --> 01:35:07,193
Kneel.

1029
01:35:11,520 --> 01:35:13,822
Take my hand...

1030
01:35:14,016 --> 01:35:19,548
...and swear eternal loyalty to Zod.

1031
01:35:57,982 --> 01:35:59,291
He switched it.

1032
01:35:59,901 --> 01:36:01,756
He did it to them.

1033
01:36:02,462 --> 01:36:07,645
The lights were on out here
while he was safe in there.

1034
01:36:08,957 --> 01:36:10,866
Hey, you know something?

1035
01:36:11,197 --> 01:36:13,238
You're a real pain in the neck!

1036
01:36:22,782 --> 01:36:24,505
Are you all right?

1037
01:36:25,628 --> 01:36:29,208
I knew you'd double-cross me, Luthor.
A lying weasel like you couldn't resist.

1038
01:36:29,661 --> 01:36:31,449
Who, me? Are you kidding?

1039
01:36:31,613 --> 01:36:35,508
Hey, I was with you all the
time. That was beautiful.

1040
01:36:35,677 --> 01:36:37,749
Did you see the way
they fell into our trap?

1041
01:36:37,981 --> 01:36:40,316
Too late, Luthor. Too late.

1042
01:36:40,573 --> 01:36:43,639
Look. Look, Superman.

1043
01:36:44,061 --> 01:36:45,948
I got a proposition for you.

1044
01:36:46,109 --> 01:36:48,346
Now, don't stop me
till you've heard this...

1045
01:36:48,509 --> 01:36:51,639
...because I know I owe you one,
but we're in the North Pole, right?

1046
01:38:05,691 --> 01:38:07,185
Look, Lois...

1047
01:38:08,282 --> 01:38:10,486
No regrets, okay? I did it.

1048
01:38:10,651 --> 01:38:13,138
I got the man I loved to love me.

1049
01:38:15,930 --> 01:38:19,442
- Didn't I?
- Oh, yeah.

1050
01:38:21,529 --> 01:38:24,147
Well, okay then. Those people need you.

1051
01:38:24,313 --> 01:38:26,615
Do you think I don't understand that?

1052
01:38:30,905 --> 01:38:35,127
We can still see each other, you know.
I mean, all the time.

1053
01:38:37,401 --> 01:38:39,571
But it just can't be...

1054
01:39:01,111 --> 01:39:03,250
Just don't forget, that's all.

1055
01:39:04,056 --> 01:39:05,365
Don't ever forget.

1056
01:39:28,856 --> 01:39:31,888
- Well, here we are.
- Home sweet home.

1057
01:39:33,048 --> 01:39:36,363
- See you at work in the morning.
- Bright and early, huh?

1058
01:39:36,535 --> 01:39:40,277
- The same old Clark and the same old Lois.
- Yup.

1059
01:39:41,046 --> 01:39:45,868
Except... maybe I won't be
quite so mean to you from now on.

1060
01:39:53,237 --> 01:39:54,448
You don't have to worry.

1061
01:39:54,998 --> 01:39:56,524
Your secret's safe with me.

1062
01:39:57,750 --> 01:40:01,165
I know. I know that, Lois.

1063
01:40:25,365 --> 01:40:27,666
Well, there he goes, kid.

1064
01:40:28,564 --> 01:40:30,452
Up, up and away.

1065
01:41:52,402 --> 01:41:55,085
- No!
- No!

1066
01:42:21,328 --> 01:42:23,368
- Hey, is Mr. White free?
- On the telephone.

1067
01:42:23,536 --> 01:42:27,311
- He's in conference at the moment.
- Yeah, that's what he says.

1068
01:42:42,991 --> 01:42:45,097
All right, give me three carbons of that.

1069
01:42:45,264 --> 01:42:47,500
- Hi.
- It's gonna be an insert in the paper.

1070
01:42:47,664 --> 01:42:49,322
That's what they said.

1071
01:42:50,800 --> 01:42:53,166
Good morning. Hi.

1072
01:42:58,608 --> 01:43:00,168
Good morning, Lois.

1073
01:43:05,647 --> 01:43:07,403
- Good morning, Lois.
- Hi, Clark.

1074
01:43:07,567 --> 01:43:10,185
Jeepers, I have seen
some faraway looks in my time...

1075
01:43:10,351 --> 01:43:13,449
...but with that look, you might as well
be on the North Pole.

1076
01:43:14,383 --> 01:43:16,488
The North Pole.

1077
01:43:17,646 --> 01:43:19,173
No, that's too silly.

1078
01:43:20,111 --> 01:43:25,478
Did you ever feel like you knew something
that was so important that...

1079
01:43:25,806 --> 01:43:27,562
No, you never did.

1080
01:43:28,334 --> 01:43:33,800
I mean, I feel like I'm sitting on the single
most important story of my career...

1081
01:43:33,965 --> 01:43:35,973
...and I can't remember what it is.

1082
01:43:36,493 --> 01:43:39,941
Well, knowing you,
it must have been about Superman.

1083
01:43:40,110 --> 01:43:43,241
Maybe how he saved the city or
saved the world or saved the universe.

1084
01:43:43,405 --> 01:43:47,180
Clark, Clark. Listen.
Jealousy's really counterproductive.

1085
01:43:47,341 --> 01:43:49,926
Now, there's some things
that you can do too.

1086
01:43:50,893 --> 01:43:52,419
Oh, yeah?

1087
01:43:52,589 --> 01:43:55,240
Really? Like what?

1088
01:43:56,685 --> 01:43:57,831
Get us a pizza.

1089
01:43:58,573 --> 01:44:02,151
- A pizza. Now?
- Yeah, I'm hungry.

1090
01:44:02,606 --> 01:44:05,027
Actually, I don't think
Mr. White would like it if...

1091
01:44:05,197 --> 01:44:07,052
I'll pay for half of it, all right?

1092
01:44:07,213 --> 01:44:08,587
I'm going.

1093
01:44:13,549 --> 01:44:14,923
Lois?

1094
01:44:15,372 --> 01:44:16,617
You know, about the pizza?

1095
01:44:17,837 --> 01:44:21,132
It's okay. I'll pay for the whole thing.

1096
01:44:23,244 --> 01:44:25,153
You know, you're really super.

1097
01:44:45,963 --> 01:44:48,265
- Hey, Ron.
- Yeah?

1098
01:44:48,428 --> 01:44:50,151
Give me another
plate of this garbage.

1099
01:44:50,315 --> 01:44:52,966
Garbage? That's my
number-one special, Rocky.

1100
01:44:53,163 --> 01:44:56,643
All right. Get me some
more coffee too, will you?

1101
01:44:57,899 --> 01:45:02,055
Gee, that's funny. I've never
seen garbage eat garbage before.

1102
01:45:09,770 --> 01:45:13,512
Excuse me, sir. I think
you're sitting in my favorite seat.

1103
01:45:13,674 --> 01:45:14,951
Come and get it, four-eyes.

1104
01:45:19,402 --> 01:45:21,093
Now cool it, Rocky.

1105
01:45:22,217 --> 01:45:23,298
Take it easy, will you?

1106
01:45:23,466 --> 01:45:26,761
I just had this joint fixed.
It cost me a fortune.

1107
01:45:42,698 --> 01:45:44,706
Oh, God!

1108
01:45:55,945 --> 01:45:57,984
This order's to go.

1109
01:46:05,417 --> 01:46:09,127
I'm terribly sorry
about all the damage, sir.

1110
01:46:11,400 --> 01:46:15,142
I've been working out.

